  <thingsToDo><![CDATA[<p>The region produces most of Italy’s olive oil and you’ll see olive trees wherever you look, some more than 1,000 years old! You can visit some of these farms and see the traditional ways of making olive oil. Another must-do is spending time in Bari where ladies will sit on the street making orecchiette, or ‘little ears’, Puglia’s pasta.</p>
<p>Puglia’s wines have come a long way. Once they were only available in Puglia itself but you’ll now find them taking pride of place in many wine lists across the UK. Nothing beats trying them in their home though and one of the best places to do this is Enoteca Thalos in Alberobello. Step inside the trullo and enjoy a tasting of three of four wines, paired with delicious local food. Gino is a master in his field and will explain the wines as he pours.</p>
<p>(above is old content from the region page that can be used)</p>]]></thingsToDo>
